251.080.  Director may delegate his duties, structure department, appoint committees. — The director may:
  (1)  Delegate any of his functions, powers and duties to employees of the department;
  (2)  Structure the department as may be required in order to carry out the purposes of sections 251.010 to 251.440 and any other duties as are assigned to the department;
  (3)  Appoint such advisory committees as may be required by various federal programs in order to carry out the purposes of sections 251.010 to 251.440.
(L. 1967 p. 357 § 8) 
Transfer of duties, 226.007, 660.010
